    <briefdescription>
<para>Forward Windows termination events to a regular worker thread. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Console-control callbacks only enqueue a lightweight event. A watcher thread invokes the configured callback in a normal thread context, where terminal cleanup can safely use locks and iostreams. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
